  "description": "The quiz assesses knowledge of HTML5 semantic elements, testing the ability to differentiate and correctly use tags beyond basic <div> and <span>. It is positioned as a moderate‑difficulty challenge with a light‑hearted, motivational tone that encourages learners to improve their markup skills. The content is aimed at developers who want to validate and deepen their HTML5 expertise.",
  "topics": [
    "HTML5 semantic tags",
    "Proper use of <header>, <nav>, <section>, <article>, <footer>, etc.",
    "Accessibility considerations",
    "Best practices for structured markup"
  ],
  "audience": "Front‑end developers, web designers, and anyone with basic HTML experience seeking to advance their semantic HTML proficiency."
}
